Given the root of a Binary Search Tree (BST) and an integer value, insert the value into the BST and return the root of the updated tree. A BST has the property that all nodes in the left subtree are less than the node, and all nodes in the right subtree are greater.

Example:
  Input:  root = [4,2,7,1,3], val = 5
  Output: [4,2,7,1,3,5]

Assume this TreeNode class:
  class TreeNode {
      int val;
      TreeNode left, right;
      TreeNode(int val) { this.val = val; }
  }

Write a method with this signature:
  public TreeNode insert(TreeNode root, int val)

